Overview
This project utilizes React along with React Bootstrap and React Icons to create a web-based invoice generation system. Follow the steps below to set up and run the application.

Prerequisites
Node.js installed on your machine.
Basic understanding of React development.
Installation Steps
Clone the Repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone <repository_url>
cd invoice-generation-app
Install Dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Configure Environment Variables (if applicable):

If your project requires any environment variables (e.g., API keys), create a .env file in the root directory and add them there.
Running the Application
Start the Development Server:

bash
Copy code
npm start
This command starts the development server and opens the application in your default web browser.

View the Application:
Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000 (or another port specified in the console) to view the running application.

Usage
Navigate Through the Application:
Explore different features and functionalities related to invoice generation.
Use React Bootstrap components for UI elements and React Icons for iconography as per project requirements.
Customization and Development
Customize Components and Styles:

Modify components in the src/components directory to suit specific requirements.
Adjust styles using CSS or SCSS files located in src/styles.
Integrate Additional Functionality:

Extend the application with additional features such as PDF generation, API integrations (if applicable), or enhanced user interactions.
Additional Notes
Ensure all dependencies are installed correctly using npm install before starting the application.
Refer to React Bootstrap and React Icons documentation for detailed usage of components and icons respectively.
